{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}For Tag - Wisp Template Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>For Tag</h1>

<p>The for tag iterates over arrays, slices, maps, or ranges.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre><code>{% for .item in .items %}...{% end %}
{% for .index, .item in .items %}...{% end %}</code></pre>

<h2>Description</h2>
<p>Creates a loop that iterates over each element in an array, slice, map, or range expression.</p>

<h2>Parameters</h2>
<ul>
  <li><code>.item</code> - Variable name for current item</li>
  <li><code>.items</code> - Array, slice, map, or range to iterate</li>
  <li><code>.index</code> - Optional variable name for current index (0-based)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Examples</h2>

<h3>Basic Array Iteration</h3>
<pre><code>{% for .item in .items %}
{%.item%}
{% end %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Input:</strong> <code>{"items": ["apple", "banana", "cherry"]}</code></p>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> apple banana cherry</p>

<h3>With Index</h3>
<pre><code>{% for .index, .item in .items %}
{%.index%}: {%.item%}
{% end %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Input:</strong> <code>{"items": ["a", "b", "c"]}</code></p>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> 0: a 1: b 2: c</p>

<h3>Map Iteration</h3>
<pre><code>{% for .key, .value in .user %}
{%.key%}: {%.value%}
{% end %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Input:</strong> <code>{"user": {"name": "Alice", "email": "alice@example.com"}}</code></p>

<h3>Range Loop</h3>
<pre><code>{% for .i in (range 1 5) %}
{%.i%}
{% end %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> 1 2 3 4 5</p>

<h3>Empty Array with else</h3>
<pre><code>{% for .item in .items %}
{%.item%}
{% else %}
No items found
{% end %}</code></pre>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Loop variable is created in current scope</li>
  <li>Index starts at 0</li>
  <li>For maps, both key and value are available</li>
  <li>Use <code>break</code> to exit early</li>
  <li>Use <code>continue</code> to skip iteration</li>
  <li><code>else</code> block executes when iterable is empty</li>
</ul>

